HEADWORD: Landlordism
<hw>Land"lord`ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The state of
being a landlord; the characteristics of a landlord; specifically, in
Great Britain, the relation of landlords to tenants, especially as
regards leased agricultural lands.</def> <rj><au>J. S.
Mill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Landlordry</ent>⟦br⟧
